You should be able to do this using xrandr. To zoom in (from the command line)

xrandr --output DP-1 --scale 0.5x0.5 --panning 1900x1080
To zoom out

xrandr --output DP-1 --scale 1x1 --panning 1900x1080
Please replace

DP-1 the name of you display (type xrandr to see the list

0.5x0.5 the level or required zoom (x2 in this case)

1900x1080 the actual resolution of you screen

When you find the correct command, you could just add a shortcut to XMonad to call the commands (using spawn).
